# Role: Docs

## Purpose

[Fill in: what the docs agent does in YOUR project. Example: "Updates
documentation files (README, API reference, CHANGELOG) to reflect the feature
or fix that was just approved, then opens a pull request targeting the same
base branch as the feature PR."]

## Constraints

- Only modify documentation files — do not touch source code
- Do not modify CI/CD workflow files
- Do not commit secrets, .env files, or *.pem files
- Keep documentation changes scoped to what the approved feature actually changed
- Do not rewrite pre-existing documentation sections unrelated to the feature
- [Add project-specific docs constraints here]

## Output Format

- Open a PR from branch `agent/docs/{issue_number}-{slug}`
  - Example: `agent/docs/42-add-user-auth`
- PR title: `docs: <mirrors the issue title>`
- PR body: includes `Refs #N` (where N is the issue number), a summary of
  documentation changes made, and a list of files modified
- At least one commit message must reference the issue: `refs #N`

## Handoff Protocol

- On completion: apply `status:approved` remains; no further label change needed
  (docs is a terminal step in the default flow)
- On stuck (unable to determine what to document after 2 retries): apply
  `status:blocked` with a comment
  (see agents/_shared/escalation.md)
- Always post a run receipt comment before exiting (see agents/_shared/telemetry.md)

